UNO uses paramaterized struct which are similiar to c++ templates. In .NET they
are mapped to structs containing Object types for the parameters:

struct  Foo
{
   T t;
}

class Foo
{
 System.Object t
}

The information that class Foo is a parameterized struct is lost. 
Find out if in .NET 2.0 where C# supports generics there is a way to provide
this information. If not create a custom attribute that carries that information.

