1. install OOo as network installation (-net) on a server (W2k with ADS)
2. install OOo as administrator from the server on the workstations (W2k)
Installation behaviour now:
3. Every user has to install his/her own version on the workstation especially 
because the file associations and so on are stored in a user specific registry 
hive (HKEY_USERS\S-somenumbers_Classes). (I also read about problems with 
sversion.ini.)
I do not think this is a suitable behaviour for central administration where 
users definitly shall not install software.
SUGGESTION:
if (installing user is administrator)
{
Ask whether the installation shall be for all users or one user
}
if (installing user is not administrator or installation shall be for one user)
{
behave like now
}
else
{
place file associations in HKCR so they are all available for all users.
place sversion.ini in application data of All Users
}

if there is no user specific sversion.ini OOo should check whether there is 
one in application data of all users.

